<Author>JLHBelfast
<Content>Excellent Hotel! Stayed at this very centrally located hotel for 4 nights October 2008. Easy access to Las Ramblas and Gothic Quarter. On a main road, which we didnt find noisy as we were on 8th floor. Metro, Tour Bus, taxi rank and Starbucks within 2 min walk. The Port is 5 minute brisk walk. Barcelona Cathedral is directly opposite.Hotel staff were very friendly and very helpful. We had breakfast every morning, which was very fresh with a great selection of cold meats/cheeses, fresh fruit, cooked breakfast and pastries. We had dinner one night in the hotel, fresh, reasonably priced, small portions (but typical for Barcelona). Our room was small, bathroom well-sized. We didnt spend much time there so the size didnt bother us at all. No tea/coffee facilities, not sure if we were meant to have these, we didnt ask anyhow.Roof top terrace has lovely views of city, windy but pleasant to sit in sun. Didnt use Spa faciilities but seemed reasonably priced and you get 25% discount on arrival.Free internet and computers in reception. Hotel very clean, tastefully decorated, free safety deposit box in room.We couldnt fault our stay at this hotel, was perfectly located (away from las ramblas but easily accessible), clean, good food and lovely staff. Would stay here again and would recommend it to others.If you want to try Tapas, highly recommend Cal Pep in Place de Olles, 5-10 min walk from hotel. Opens at 8 on weeknights, expensive but a great experience! 
