<Content>Great hotel, great location! We stayed 5 nights in the Montcada and we'd be happy to recommend it to anyone. OK, our double room was pretty small but we didn't spent a great deal of time there. There's just so much to see in Barcelona and thanks to the great location at the Montcada you can step out of the door and start enjoying the city. The staff were friendly and efficient, the place was spotlessly clean and the breakfast (served form 0730-1030) was great. Our room had everything we needed. (We don't do cat-swinging.) There's a safe for storing valuables which actually got stuck one night but we had a member of staff up to fix it within minutes. The bathroom was spacious and the shower was great. Biggest advantage of the Montcada has to be it's superb location just opposite the Cathedral and within easy walking distance of loads of attractions, bars, restaurants and shops. 
